article.linkText: Minor scores 15 in SIU Edwardsville's 67-58 victory over Eastern Illinois
article.story: EDWARDSVILLE, Ill. -- — Damarco Minor scored 15 points as SIU Edwardsville beat Eastern Illinois 67-58 on Friday night. Minor also contributed 10 rebounds for the Cougars (8-6). Shamar Wright scored 14 points while shooting 4 for 7 (3 for 4 from 3-point range) and 3 of 3 from the free throw line, and added three blocks. Terrance Thompson was 4 of 9 shooting and 4 of 6 from the free throw line to finish with 12 points. The Panthers (6-8, ) were led in scoring by Kyndall Davis, who finished with 23 points. Corey Swayer Jr. added 11 points and four steals for Eastern Illinois. In addition, Kooper Jacobi finished with seven points and seven rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
